## Install Docker

Install docker/ or check if we can do with minkikube, kubeadm which have already installed docker for kubernetes

## Create Docker file
Pull a base image from docker hub
you can check for images at docker hub
https://hub.docker.com
https://hub.docker.com/_/ubuntu/

docker pull [OPTIONS] NAME[:TAG|@DIGEST]
docker pull ubuntu:16.04

mkdir flask_app
cd flask_app
sudo vim DockerFile
write the docker file
flask_app 
-hello-world.py
-requirements.txt
Dockerfile

Build the app 
sudo docker build -t hello-world:v2 .

start the container
sudo docker run -d -p 3773:5000 hello-world:v2

curl http://127.0.0.1:3773
